│ THOUGHT: This looks good. The logic now is:                                                                                                                                           │
│ 1. If any return instruction fails to collect versions, continue                                                                                                                      │
│ 2. If there are no return instructions at all (HasReturn is false), continue                                                                                                          │
│ 3. Otherwise, we expect Callees to be non-empty, so the assertion should hold                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ This should handle the reproducer case (no return instructions) and preserve the assertion for cases where we do have return instructions but somehow get empty Callees (which would  │
│ indicate a real bug).                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                               │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
